<Author>jpad108
<Content>An unknown Jewel My husband miscalculated how late we would be getting into Phoenix on our trek to Sedona, so I had to look around for another place to stay at the last moment. We found the Hampton quite by accident, but the location seemed perfect for our purposes.When we arrived the very pleasant manager and check-in staff hoped we had a reservation because they only had one handicapped room left. We did and they very efficiently checked us in.Despite a wedding and a golf tournament, this booked to capacity hotel was extremely quiet. the beds were wonderful, the room was clean, the hot breakfast the next morning was very good.The best part is the location if you are heading north on 17. You are next door to an outlet mall, a wal-mart, and a few fast restaurants, but you are outside the traffic of Phoenix and despite the location, we did not experience any noise at all. A very restful night's sleep.We would most definitely stay there again. 
