<Author>hjn0901
<Content>Great place to stay We staid at the Hampton inn  Suites twice last month. We had originally booked it for the first night of a one month vacation in the western US and thanks to Delta and JFK airport we arrived at the hotel at 3 am in the morningEven though the front door was locked and we had to ring the bell, the welcome was great. We got our room quickly and the night concierge even opened up the small lobby shop so we could get some water for the night. We were so impressed with the first stay that we booked a night for the final night of our vacation before flying home. Again the service was impressive. Check inn were quick and the front desk helped with boarding passes and supplied us with a card with directions to the airport.We would highly recommend this hotel, and will probably chose to stay here when we come back next time. The location next to a shopping area with lots of restaurants were a plus as well.The roomsThe rooms for both stays were identical, large and very, very clean. The beds were great, and small sofa section very nice. The bathrooms very clean and the hotel had supplied lots of good quality shampoo, lotion etc...Breakfast. The hotel breakfast is nice, with different hot items every day. It also have lots of fruits and a good supply of cereals and breads. The breakfast hostess kept the breakfast area nice and tidy all the time. 
