<Content>expensive but worth it As soon as we saw the huge room, our decision was made. High ceilings make everything look bigger but we really appreciated the 2 phones, the lounge area and fridge and micro. The bathroom was a liitle small and we did have some problems that were sorted immediately. The bath water only trickled away, the tv was plugged in wrongly and I got stuck in the bathroom! The breakfast choices are varied especially if you have children. The outlet centre is almost opposite and that is worth a visit just to look at the beautifully manicured gardens. Anthem is a growing town and there's little for the tourist. Thoroughly recommend the Asianakitchen restaurant. Huge Asian dishes which are cheap and extremely well presented. Lake Pleasant is close and beautiful.At check-out, I did mention that the pool had not been cleaned but I'm sure by just mentioning it, the maintenance men will be there immediately! 
