<Author>Mrlvr
<Content>Was great through and through Wow. I havent needed to stay at a hotel in a while, but glad I chose this one. As soon as I walked in, I of course asked for the rate. I really didnt want to spend that much, after all I only needed a nights sleep. However I am soo glad I did decide to stay. I was on my way up to Sedona and had an appt the next morning. And after all day at a Phoenix water park didnt really want to drive. The 2 queen beds were perfect. So much room. The staff is in every way awesome. Literally everyone I met was great and friendly. Very Roomy in rm 111. The new overstuffed bedding, with a choice of hard pillows on one bed and soft on the other and a note just to call if you needed more or to change what was there, Great! There is even a small lap table to use your laptop on. And the computer room is great. Though only one computer. It has printer, fax, internet, phone etc. Everything ready to completely do your work if needed. (and I did need to do a little). Tis a pool facing rm on first floor, but was very quiet. There is a small store with a few other necessities if you need to buy something, (from juices to food etc.)along with a workout room with 3 machines. As previously mentioned, Iron/brd in armoire, nice refrigerator already on, along with air condition in room. Nice touch after having been outside all day. The bathroom was good. It had the new arched outward shower curtain bar for more room inside the tub. Plenty of soft towels. Forgot my toothpaste and front desk gentleman provided quickly with no problems. The only thing I thought was missing was although there was a fan in the bathroom, it is the automatic kind, that is slow to me. I would have preferred the one with a switch, that kind is faster. The breakfast again was great. So many choices, along with reg/decaf coffee and also Extra Strong. I was a little sad there was no pancakes that day, but the lady explained how the breakfast changed daily, and the next day there would be! I almost stayed another night. The fruit was great and fresh along with all the breads. Even if you get up late they have a prepared breakfast to go bag waiting for you at the desk when checking out.! Great.... But my most rememerable experience was all the staff. The late front desk manager, who talked me into staying. everyone. She did note that their hotel was the last one for the next hour heading north. And in driving the next day, this was the truth. And as everyone knows it is the staff that can make or break a delightful stay. Even if things are horribly wrong, a great staff can more than make up for it. And I feel that if something had gone horribly wrong, the staff would have turned it right around.There is a Walmart, Denny's and even a Car Repair shop within walking distance. So again All in All a wonderful stay. Thanks Hampton!! 
