<Author>TroyzWife
<Content>Great experience start to finish! We arrived at the hotel at 11:45pm, as I walked through the front doors, the front deskman said Welcome to the Hampton Inn, you must be Troy  Christi lastname. That was a wonderful touch, like we were expected and welcome. Granted it was very late and we were the 2nd to the last checkin, but after driving almost 7 hours it made me smile. Everyone was very accomodating- when our iron quit working the maid had one there in 5 minutes, so how could you possibly unhappy the iron didn't work?The lobby is nicely decorated with big comfy sofas, the room to the east is where breakfast is served. It is a GREAT breakfast. It is typical serve yourself, but what they offer is no where near typical. They have cold cereal, hot cereal, eggs, salsa, ketchup, sausage, bagels, different types of breads to toast, crescents, jellies, butter, margerine, 3 types of coffees, flavored creamers, hot teas, apple juice, oj, fresh cut up fruit, hot teas, milk, On sunday they also had bisquits and gravy. I think the eggs were powdered, but I am NOT complaining! My husband and I left pleasantly full- a great way to start the day. Our room was a King/study. As you walk in first is the closet and bathroom, then is a living room type area, with a fold out sofa, microwave, refrigerator, that you can actually use, coffee maker, a nice desk w/internet hookup. The bedroom area is the other half of the room, the king size bed was roomy, there is an armoire for more closet space and the iron/board. The tv is located in the bedroom half of the room but can be swiveled to face the sofa.Location is PERFECT for visting family in Anthem so you don't have to drive from Phoenix which is quite aways away. There is a Denny's and Del Taco sharing the Driveway/Street with the hotel. It is across the street from the Anthem Outlet mall which is AWESOME, among the many stores I found Ann Taylor, Gap,lots more. A two minute drive on the same street is a SUPER Walmart- being from California I had never experienced a SUPER Walmart before and I LOVED it!!IMHO it was better than Hyatts that we've stayed at.Highly Recommended 
